Nice for s stroll

Nice little park but perhaps not really interesting for children. I often pass there with my dog ‚Äã‚Äãwhen we are out walking. The park is mainly frequented by humans accompanied by their dogs, who are also allowed but kept on a leash.

if you want a peaceful time where you can completely forget that you are in paris, this is for you ‚ò∫Ô∏è very quiet and few people!

Nice park in which dog lovers can run/play their dog with the whole gang of dogs in the park who are very sociable and ready to have fun. A rare event in Paris that does dogs a lot of good. Don't forget to pick up ;)
A park, more like a wasteland, some days you have characters doing their business quietly and other days the municipal police chasing elderly people with their dogs.

A great place for dogs. Yes, it's marked "dog on a leash" but in 13th, no dog park and this small park becomes the park for dogs by default: there is no playground or any entertainment for children or adults. big, but a little space for doggies. Recently, municipal officials have been fining owners of off-leash dogs: shame on the municipal administration which only punishes but does not propose anything for the well-being of the neighborhood dogs!
Wildflowers bloom on this old railway line
A small park where you can relax and sunbathe.... When it's there!

Small but original park thanks to the presence of rails from an old Parisian railway line, an element that children really like. There are some very ergonomic wooden benches scattered around the park, ideal for lying down and reading a book outdoors.
Nice. Dogs are allowed, finally. It's a shame it isn't longer.
Nice place for dog walking, the right place to meet and chat with other Parisian doggie owners. The downside is that there is little shade. No interest, however, for children.

A pretty little park in Paris, but it's really the little one. There are 500 m of rail of the small belt and that's it. a bit short of a section, but obviously they are working on the rest of the section, so waiting for a nice larger park to open :)
We walk our dog there, too many spikelets at the moment, we can't let him go, it seeps into the hairs and orifices.  Small green space, lots of dogs, Too bad it's not well maintained.
Very pretty little old path with the rails, there are people taking a little break and other naps, an ideal corner for a quiet moment.  *Even better if there are entertainment.
Good for walking your dog there, there are a lot of dogs there although it is forbidden to release the dogs, we do it anyway because there is no reason why they must absolutely be kept on a leash.

Small belt reused as a public garden, well laid out although there is still a lack of vegetation, all unfortunately disturbed by the noise emanating from Boulevard Kellerman (car traffic, tram and park users who listen to music on an external hp or make loud telephone calls) .
One of the very rare places for my best friend
Nice, but limited space, there are other accesses to the small belt which are larger
Fairly quiet and it's a great place for dogs, too bad it's mandatory that they be on a leash
A lovely discovery that runs along the outer boulevard on the line of the small ring road. Arrange so that it is alive. Very good and quiet
Discreet and grassy square along the small belt. Doggies are welcome with or without a leash. There is grass and a few benches.
Very pleasant, we quickly went around but this corner is a haven of peace
open non-stop all summer to cool off... nice stroll to go to Pte d'Italie on foot
Original walk but the tunnels should not be accessible to pedestrians because it is without lighting and quite gloomy
it's a good idea to reorganize it into a park version for the children; they are delighted to walk around or ride their bike or scooter.

This section of the small ring road, recently rehabilitated, offers a pleasant alternative (during the day) to walking along Boulevard Kellerman. A few benches, and the view of some of the street art along this stretch of Kellerman.
Top we can let the dogs go! A little small for a real walk
This place is magnificent, I love it, it‚Äôs my little place to wander around
Many dogs not kept on a leash, too bad
Very nice to walk around ‚ò∫Ô∏è
Beautiful walk especially in spring Popular meeting place for dogs
Very nice green space
Too bad too many dogs, my son is afraid of dogs we couldn't stay long..
Excellent place to walk with your dog
Great place to walk with the dog
